{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"result":{"protocolVersion":"2025-11-25","capabilities":{"tools":{}},"serverInfo":{"name":"medaka","version":"0.1.0-preview"}}}
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"result":{"tools":[{"name":"medaka_check","description":"Type-check Medaka source and return structured diagnostics — the same JSON `medaka check --json` emits (stable `code`, `range`, `severity`, `help`, and a machine-applicable `fix` where available). Provide exactly one of `file` or `source`.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to a .mdk file to check."},"source":{"type":"string","description":"Inline Medaka source to check (no file on disk)."}}}},{"name":"medaka_type_at","description":"Infer the type/scheme at a position — the LSP hover, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style); returns the `<name> : <type>` at that point, resolving imported names against the project on disk. A position off any identifier returns a clean \"no symbol\" note, not an error.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}},{"name":"medaka_symbols","description":"List a file's top-level declarations (functions, data types, interfaces, impls, …) with their source ranges — the LSP document-symbol outline, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path; parse-only (no typecheck), so it works even on a file with type errors. A multi-clause function collapses to ONE entry (its signature + all clauses), not one-per-clause. A file that fails to PARSE returns a distinct isError result — `{\"parseError\": true, \"line\", \"col\", \"message\"}` — so you can tell an empty/no-decl file (empty list) from a broken one (parseError). Each entry's `range` covers the whole declaration (line-granular, `character` 0); `selectionRange` is the declaration's real name-token span (real `character` column, #331) when the parser could resolve one, else the same whole-decl range (e.g. an `impl` head with no interface-implementing type at all — never seen in valid syntax). For `impl Iface Type where`, `selectionRange` points at `Type`'s own name — the leftmost type constructor, even when it sits inside parens or ahead of further type arguments (`impl Eq (List a) where` blames `List`; `impl Index (MutArray a) Int where` blames `MutArray`, not `Int`) — falling back to the `impl` keyword itself only for a fully-parametric head with no type constructor anywhere (`impl Iface a where`). Child symbols (variant ctors, record fields, interface/impl methods, let-binds) each carry their OWN name-token span for both `range` and `selectionRange`, falling back to the parent's range only where the parser could not resolve one.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to list symbols for."}},"required":["file"]}},{"name":"medaka_definition","description":"Find the declaration that defines the identifier at a position — the LSP go-to-definition, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style). INTRA-FILE ONLY: it scans declarations in this same file, so a use of a name defined in ANOTHER file returns an empty result rather than a wrong location. A position off any identifier also returns an empty result.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}},{"name":"medaka_references","description":"Find every use of the identifier at a position, ACROSS THE WHOLE PROJECT — the LSP find-references, driven statelessly, read-only. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style); optionally `includeDeclaration` (boolean, default true) to include the symbol's own declaration site. Resolves through binder identity (scopes + import origin), not spelling, so it is correct under shadowing (an inner binder's uses never include an outer same-named one), import aliasing (`import m as A; A.f` and a bare `f` both resolve to the same symbol), and same-name-in-different-modules (no cross-contamination). INTRA-PROJECT ONLY (F1): a stdlib/prelude symbol's project-internal uses are returned, but the index never descends into stdlib bodies. Best-effort (F2): an unparseable sibling file is skipped rather than failing the whole query. Returns a JSON array of `{uri, range}` objects (one per use, `uri` a `file://` path) across every file it appears in; empty `[]` for a position off any identifier or one that resolves to nothing indexed — never a crash, never a wrong hit. NEVER writes to disk.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."},"includeDeclaration":{"type":"boolean","description":"Include the symbol's own declaration site in the result. Default true."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}},{"name":"medaka_fmt","description":"Format Medaka source with the compiler's canonical formatter (`medaka fmt`), driven statelessly. Provide exactly one of `file` or `source`. NEVER writes to disk — a `file` argument is only READ, never opened for writing; apply the returned text yourself if you want it saved. Default: returns the formatted source text. Pass `check: true` to instead get a clean/dirty verdict (`{\"clean\": true|false}`) without the full text. Input that fails to PARSE returns an isError result carrying the parse diagnostic, never a crash.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to a .mdk file to format. READ ONLY — the file is never written; the formatted text is returned for the caller to apply."},"source":{"type":"string","description":"Inline Medaka source to format (no file on disk)."},"check":{"type":"boolean","description":"If true, report clean/dirty instead of returning the formatted text (default false)."}}}},{"name":"medaka_lint","description":"Run the compiler's style linter (`medaka lint`) over one or more files and return structured diagnostics — the same JSON envelope `medaka_check`/`medaka lint --json` emit (stable `range`/`severity`/`source`, with the lint RULE NAME in `code`). Give `paths` (array of file paths); optionally narrow with comma-separated `deny`/`only`/`disable` rule-name lists (mirror the CLI's --deny/--only/--disable). Report-only — no autofix; apply a fix yourself if you want one.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"paths":{"type":"array","items":{"type":"string"},"description":"Paths to .mdk files to lint."},"deny":{"type":"string","description":"Comma-separated rule names to promote to error severity (mirrors --deny)."},"only":{"type":"string","description":"Comma-separated rule names to keep, dropping findings from every other rule (mirrors --only)."},"disable":{"type":"string","description":"Comma-separated rule names to suppress (mirrors --disable)."}},"required":["paths"]}},{"name":"medaka_test","description":"Run a file's doctests (and property tests, if any) and return structured PER-EXAMPLE results. Give a `file` path. Runs DOCTESTS and PROPERTY tests only — bare `test \"…\"` decls are NOT run here (they run under the human `medaka test` command). ⚠️ RESULTS ARE UNDER THE INTERPRETER (eval), NOT the native backend — a native-only miscompile is INVISIBLE here (a file can show every doctest green over a grammar the native binary silently mis-lowers, #81), so treat these as \"passes UNDER EVAL\", never an unqualified \"passes\". Returns `{file, engine:\"eval\", note, doctests:{total,passed,failed,errors,examples:[{line,input,status:pass|fail|error,expected?,actual?,detail?}]}, properties:[{name,status,detail}], summary:{passed,failed,ok}}`. A property's FAILING counterexample is RNG-dependent (non-portable). `isError` is true iff any doctest or property did not pass.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file whose doctests (and property tests, if any) to run."}},"required":["file"]}}]}}
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"error":{"code":-32601,"message":"Unknown tool: bogus_tool"}}
